currentDoc: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

currentSuggestions.original: The bee looks at you and says "I did, Your Majesty."
currentSuggestions.trimmed: The bee looks at you and says "I did, Your Majesty."

ops.insert: The bee looks at you and says "I did, Your Majesty."

currentSuggestions.original: The bee looks at you with his tiny black eyes and says "No, Your Majesty.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: The bee looks at you with his tiny black eyes and says "No, Your Majesty.

currentSuggestions.original: "No, Your Majesty," the bee says, "I am your loyal servant.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: "No, Your Majesty," the bee says, "I am your loyal servant.
